questions.question: So the natural next basic question is, what is the what is deep reinforcement learning?
And what is this idea of using neural networks to deal with this huge incoming stream?
Do you have good intuition about why it works at all and works as well as it does?
Am I surprised that our current systems can do as well as they can do?
Is there interesting things that come to memory in terms of the play of the human or the machine?
So how big of an intellectual leap was this, that self-play could achieve superhuman level performance on its own?
